<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870915-0141 </DOCNO><HL> Boeing Co. Unit Gets$235.5 Million in WorkFrom the Air Force</HL><DD> 09/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BA XON ASH MRN GQ RTN ROK GD UTX MD TXI BDMAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Boeing Aerospace Co., a unit of Boeing Co., won a $235.5 million Air Force contract for test and program support for railroad basing of MX missiles.    Exxon Co. USA, a unit of Exxon Corp., was issued a $130.3 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    BDM Corp. received a $64.1 million Army contract for missile-defense technical support services.    The Holmes andamp; Narver Inc. unit of Ashland Oil Inc. and Morrison-Knudsen Corp. won a $49.4 million Army contract for support services at Redstone Arsenal, Ala.    Grumman Aerospace Corp., a unit of Grumman Corp., got a $32.5 million Navy contract for EA-6B aircraft support equipment.    Raytheon Co. received Navy contracts totaling $18.7 million for Sparrow missile improvements and Phoenix missile production equipment.    Units of Rockwell International Corp. were given contracts totaling $18.1 million for space shuttle support services and aircraft-engineering services for the Air Force, and logistics-planning services for the Navy.    Baham Corp. was awarded a $15.1 million Navy contract for engineering services.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. won a $14.8 million Navy contract for Harpoon missile support equipment.    Pratt andamp; Whitney, a unit of United Technologies Corp., received Air Force contracts totaling $11.7 million for aircraft engine parts.    General Dynamics Corp. got Air Force contracts totaling $11.1 million for F-16 aircraft improvements.    Texas Instruments Inc. was awarded a $10.5 million Army contract for M-48 tank equipment.    Johns Hopkins University received a $10 million Navy contract for research and engineering services. </TEXT></DOC>